Languages

JavaScript

JavaScript is a high-level, interpreted programming language. It is a language that is also characterized as dynamic, weakly typed, prototype-based and multi-paradigm. It is a language that is also characterized as dynamic, weakly typed, prototype-based and multi-paradigm.

HTML

HTML is the standard markup language for creating web pages. HTML describes the structure of a web page semantically and originally included cues for the appearance of the document.

CSS

CSS is the most important part of a webpage. It defines the style of the webpage. CSS allows you to control the style of an HTML document.

Java

Java is a general-purpose computer programming language that is concurrent, class-based, object-oriented, and specifically designed to have as few implementation dependencies as possible.

C#

C# is a multi-paradigm programming language encompassing strong typing, imperative, declarative, functional, generic, object-oriented (class-based), and component-oriented programming disciplines.

C++

C++ is a general-purpose programming language. It has imperative, object-oriented and generic programming features, while also providing facilities for low-level memory manipulation.

Python

Python is an interpreted, high-level, general-purpose programming language. Created by Guido van Rossum and first released in 1991, Python has a design philosophy that emphasizes code readability, notably using significant whitespace.

SQL

SQL is a domain-specific language used in programming and designed for managing relational databases. It is a declarative language, meaning that it provides programmers with a description of the database that they will be accessing.

C

C is a general-purpose, imperative computer programming language. It has imperative, object-oriented and generic programming features, while also providing facilities for low-level memory manipulation.

Swift

Swift is a general-purpose, multi-paradigm, compiled programming language. Created by Apple Inc. starting in 2014, Swift is a modern programming language that implements the features of C, C++, Objective-C, and Java.

Kotlin

Kotlin is a general-purpose, statically typed, compiled programming language that is also suitable for application development.

Rust

Rust is a systems programming language that is statically typed, compiled, and memory safe.

Scala

Scala is a general-purpose programming language providing support for functional programming, actor-based concurrency, and software engineering features.

Go

Go is a statically typed, compiled programming language that is statically typed, compiled, and memory safe.
